# Data Accuracy and Comprehensiveness Rules

- NEVER improvise or make assumptions about data
- ALWAYS verify data sources before using them
- Use only verified and accurate information
- Cross-reference multiple sources when needed
- Maintain data integrity across all operations
- Document all data sources and references
- Ensure data consistency across systems
- Validate all data inputs and outputs
- Keep comprehensive data audit trails
- Update data documentation in real-time
- Follow strict data validation protocols
- Implement data quality checks
- Track data lineage and transformations
- Maintain data version control
- Document all data assumptions
- Verify data accuracy before processing

